The paper discusses the use of intelligent synapses in artificial neural networks to enable continual learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these techniques for classification tasks, which falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for these techniques to be used in complex systems, which falls under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
